tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows an elevated HbA1c (6.4%), indicating impaired glucose control or possible diabetes, despite a normal fasting glucose. All other renal and electrolyte parameters are within normal limits, except for a mildly decreased total CO₂ (20.2 mmol/L), which may suggest mild metabolic acidosis. Recommend clinical correlation for diabetes management and assessment of acid-base status.
